{"source_key":"sha256-57a0ef58ecdd57e62937c2289b37339b","record_index":283,"record_hash":"sha256:9e0ace9cb3be3ec38de56ac45645cfe50d80d3e9ca52a6ed30af855f2fc9c47d","timestamp":"2026-05-26T11:34:34.498Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_kind":"file_edit","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: [REDACTED:path]\n@@\n-**Status:** open · needs upstream fix\n+**Status:** resolved upstream in `but-agentlog` (`57863c1985` / PR #13943) and consumed by Agent Trail by pinning GitButler `[REDACTED:entropy]`.\n@@\n-## TL;DR\n+## TL;DR\n+\n+This is a historical bug report. The missing-start-of-session symptom is fixed by the upstream\n+session-level association fallback: once a session is associated with a branch/review, older indexed\n+turns in that session can verify against the session association instead of only their own\n+per-turn `observed_targets`.\n+\n+Agent Trail must depend on a GitButler revision that includes that fallback. If it is pinned to\n+`[REDACTED:entropy]`, PR trails can still drop the first prompt for sessions\n+that started before the branch/PR existed.\n \n A coding-agent session is captured as many *turns*. Each turn is indexed under the branch / review / change targets observed **at the instant that turn is written** (`capture_environment` → `but_workspace::head_info`). When that per-turn workspace observation fails or comes back empty — which it does for the **large majority** of turns in practice — the turn is written with **empty `observed_targets`** and therefore gets **no index entry at all**.\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-26T11:34:34.498Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}